    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> still an issue on latest master\r\n\r\nYes, and we understand better now what is happening, at least we think we do: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/src/status/mailservers.nim#L244-L260.\r\n\r\nThat code is unsafe (the compiler is forced to accept it via the `{.gcsafe.}` pragma on L245). While locks are used in an attempt to make it safe, that unfortunately doesn't help. In Nim you can't safely read/write data subject to GC that's on another thread's heap. If you do, then you introduce errors/instability in the GC ref counts and the program will eventually crash with an unrecoverable error. We're running that code every 10 seconds after login, so it's just a roll of the dice as to when it will crash. Sometimes it crashes just after login, sometimes it's hours later.\r\n\r\n@emizzle and I are working to re-architect this piece. We've already eliminated all the other GC unsafe code in status-desktop, but this one is a bit more involved. We'll figure it out, stay tuned!",
